Class OldFynotekWord

java.lang.Object
com.mathmaster13.fynotek.FynotekParent
com.mathmaster13.fynotek.OldFynotekWord
public final class OldFynotekWord extends FynotekParent
A class for handling words in an older version of Fynotek. All objects created by this class are immutable. Old Fynotek documentation can be found here.

1.0

    • verbTense

      @NotNull public @NotNull OldFynotekWord verbTense(@NotNull @NotNull FynotekParent.Tense tenseOfVerb)
      Returns this OldFynotekWord inflected for the verb tense specified by tenseOfVerb. Note that verbTense(Tense.GNOMIC) and verbTense(Tense.HYP_GNOMIC) will always return the same result. This function should be called before any suffix functions, not after. If a word has previously been marked for case or tense, it usually should not be marked again. If this function is called on a marked word, a warning will be generated, and there is no guarantee for the result.
      Specified by:

    • match

      @NotNull public @NotNull OldFynotekWord match(@NotNull @NotNull FynotekParent word)
      Returns this word inflected for the same case or tense as word. This function should be called before any suffix functions, not after. If a word has previously been marked for case or tense, it usually should not be marked again. If this function is called on a marked word, a warning will be generated, and there is no guarantee for the result. If the word to be matched with is a FynotekWord marked for a noun case, this word is returned with the FynotekWord's inflection, but with FynotekParent.Ablaut.DEFAULT ablaut applied.
      Specified by:
      match in class FynotekParent
      Parameters:
      word - the FynotekParent to match this word's inflection with.
      Returns:
      this word inflected for the same case or tense as word.

    • isValidSequence

      public static boolean isValidSequence(@NotNull @NotNull String sequence)
      Returns whether the given sequence is phonotactically and orthographically valid in old Fynotek. Capitalization is ignored (for example, "A" and "a" are treated the same way). Multiple words can be separated by whitespace, and this function will only return true if all words in sequence are valid. Leading and trailing whitespace is ignored (the String.trim() method is called on sequence). A sequence containing punctuation marks, numbers, or other non-letter characters (with the exception of ') returns false, as well as an empty sequence or one containing only whitespace.
      Parameters:
      sequence - the sequence to be checked for validity.
      Returns:
      true if sequence is a valid sequence, and false if otherwise.
